text.__SUMMARY__:
Baeckea subcuneata is a shrub found along the west coast Western Australia.The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.8 to 1.5 metres (2.6 to 4.9 ft). It blooms between August and November producing white-pink flowers.
It is found on sand dunes and sandstone outcrops in the coastal parts of the Mid West region of Western Australia in a small area near Geraldton where it grows in sandy soils.The species was first formally described by the botanist Ferdinand von Mueller in 1864 in the work Fragmenta Phytographiae Australiae
